.TH "reuseport_add_sock" 9 "reuseport_add_sock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
reuseport_add_sock \- Add a socket to the reuseport group of another.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" reuseport_add_sock
.BI "(struct sock *sk "  ","
.BI "struct sock *sk2 "  ","
.BI "bool bind_inany "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
New socket to add to the group.
.IP "sk2" 12
Socket belonging to the existing reuseport group.
.IP "bind_inany" 12
Whether or not the group is bound to a local INANY address.

May return ENOMEM and not add socket to group under memory pressure.
